Asia and Pacific
---
[1] Pakistan (Sindh province)
Date: Thu 24 May 2018
Source: Pakistan Observer [edited]
https://pakobserver.net/measles-virus-kills-four-more-children/


On [Thu 24 May 2018, 4 more children died due to measles virus in Ubaro [Ghotki district] and Faiz Gunj [Khairpur district, in Sindh].

According to detail, measles virus has been spreading in low lying areas of Khairpur, Sukkur, Ghotki, and Naushahro Feroze districts and several children died in above district due to measles while hundreds of people are suffering from that virus.

Three children died in village RB Malik near Ubaro while [another child] died in village Rasool Bux Abupoto on [Thu 24 May 2018].

The villagers appealed to the authorities to send a team of doctors in affected area and save the life of their lovely children.

