Europe
---

[4] Ukraine
Date: Thu 24 May 2018
Source: Silver Telegram [edited]
https://sivtelegram.media/measles-outbreak-in-ukraine-the-number-of-cases-continues-to-grow/18036/


In Ukraine over the past week (14-20 May 2018) [the Ministry of health of Ukraine reported] 1610 measles cases (642 adults and 968 children), as reported in a press-service.

In mid-May [2018] it was reported that since the beginning of 2018 more than 15 000 people are sick with measles in Ukraine. During this time, 8 people -- 6 children and 2 adults -- have died from complications from measles.

From the beginning, most people got measles in Ivano-Frankivsk (total 2137 people: 1488 adults and 649 children); Transcarpathia (a total of 2131 people: 1711 adults and 420 children); Lviv (1785 total employees: 590 adults and 1195 children); Odessa (total 1552 person: 766 adults and 786 children); and Chernivtsi (a total of 1081 persons: 361 adults and 720 children).

[Byline: Jan Hartman]

